==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The '''TechDraw Dimension''' tool is the TechDraw equivalent of the [[Sketcher_Dimension|Sketcher Dimension]] tool. It offers contextual dimensioning and thus can replace most of the other [[TechDraw_Workbench#Dimensions|dimension tools]].

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Optionally preselect some geometric elements (vertices, edges or faces).
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_Dimension.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_Dimension|Insert Dimension]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Dimensions → [[Image:TechDraw_Dimension.svg|16px]] Insert Dimension}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|D}}.
# The cursor changes to a cross with the tool icon.
# If you have not yet selected an element: select one.
# Depending on the selected element(s) a dimension is proposed.
# Optionally select an additional element.
# The proposed dimension is updated.
# Optionally press the {{KEY|M}} key one or more times to cycle through other available dimensions, if any.
# Do one of the following:
#* Click in an empty area of the page or within the view to confirm:
#*# The clicked point determines the location of the dimension.
#*# A dimension is added.
#*# This tool runs in continue mode: optionally keep creating dimensions.
#* To finish, right-click or press {{KEY|Esc}}.

== Limitations == <!--T:8-->

<!--T:9-->
* Currently the tool can only handle 2D references (geometry selected in the drawing).


